properties.areaDesc: Sheboygan to Port Washington WI; Port Washington to North Point Light WI
properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued November 28 at 9:04PM CST until November 30 at 12:00AM CST by NWS Milwaukee/Sullivan WI
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Small Craft Advisory, south winds 15 to 25 kt
with gusts up to 30 kt and waves 6 to 9 ft expected. For the
Gale Warning, west winds 20 to 25 kt with gusts up to 40 kt and
waves 2 to 5 ft expected.

* WHERE...Nearshore Waters from Sheboygan to North Point
Lighthouse.

* WHEN...For the Small Craft Advisory, until midnight CST Tuesday
night. For the Gale Warning, from midnight Tuesday night to
midnight CST Wednesday night.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous waves which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL MIDNIGHT CST TUESDAY NIGHT... ...GALE WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM MIDNIGHT TUESDAY NIGHT TO MIDNIGHT CST WEDNESDAY NIGHT
